  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6784.62 sitting just above the 6774 flip strike in a PIN regime, dealers are long gamma and likely buying this dip after the wall break event, providing stabilizing flow. The massive +75.4B gamma wall at 6800 creates significant selling pressure on any rally attempt, while the thick positive gamma concentration between 6780-6800 should contain volatility and promote mean reversion. Key levels to watch: 6774 flip strike as support (dealer buying intensifies below) and 6800 resistance where dealer selling accelerates.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward the 6785-6795 zone with limited upside past 6800.",
